## 🔎 Overview  
This project explores the **core principles of modern database systems**, combining theory with practical design. Topics include:  

- ✅ Normalization & schema design  
- ✅ Indexing & query optimization  
- ✅ Transaction management & concurrency control  
- ✅ Storage structures & buffer management  
- ✅ Hands-on SQL examples with PostgreSQL/MySQL/SQLite  

> 🎯 The goal is to bridge the gap between *academic concepts* and *real-world database implementations*.  

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack  
- **Languages**: Python | Java | SQL  
- **Databases**: PostgreSQL | MySQL | SQLite  
- **Tools**: ER Diagrams | Query Profilers | Benchmarking Scripts  

---

## 🚀 Getting Started  

### Prerequisites  
- Python 3.8+ / Java 11+  
- PostgreSQL or MySQL installed  
- Git  

### Installation  
```bash
git clone https://github.com/kraryal/Database-Systems-Concepts---Design.git
cd Database-Systems-Concepts---Design
pip install -r requirements.txt   # if using Python
```

### Run Examples  
```bash
python src/normalization_demo.py
python src/indexing_demo.py
```

---

## 📂 Project Structure  

```
Database-Systems-Concepts-Design/
├── src/           # core implementations & demos
├── docs/          # notes, ER diagrams, theory writeups
├── schemas/       # SQL schemas & design examples
├── tests/         # unit & integration tests
├── benchmarks/    # query optimization experiments
└── README.md
```

